19/05/2005
OHRID, Macedonia -- A two-day meeting of the defence ministers of Albania, Bulgaria and Macedonia ended in Ohrid Wednesday (18 May) with a vow to strengthen co-operation. 
A joint statement stressed the countries' commitment to reforms, security and stability in the region. 
A trilateral agreement on co-operation in military training, technique and science was sealed on the first day of the meeting. 
(Macedonian Government Web site - 19/05/05; A1 TV, Telma TV - 18/05/05)
